ce:section.ce:para:
To evaluate the practical applicability of the sensing system to real samples, experiments on cow milk and milk powder samples was performed (Fig. 6
                         and Table 2
                        ).The addition of different concentration melamine into the biosensing system caused a red shift. As shown in Table 2, no melamine was detected from the analyzed milk and milk powder samples. Using the sensing system, a spiking experiment at different concentration of melamine was conducted. Table 2 showed the recovery results, indicating that the biosensing system exhibited good recovery and anti-inference. Based on the results shown above, the proposed method can be employed as a sensitive and selective method for melamine in milk samples, exhibiting promising potential for its practical application.
